00:01:38,620 --> 00:01:41,052
- Sure.
- Thanks.

19
00:01:41,052 --> 00:01:43,440
Why am I here with you lying to a kid?

20
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:46,099
We haven't even found Director Sheng yet.
[North Olympic Yacht Club]

21
00:01:46,099 --> 00:01:50,790
If you want to help someone, you should help them with all your might.

22
00:01:50,790 --> 00:01:52,729
Xia Xia.

23
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:55,446
Yanyan.

24
00:01:55,446 --> 00:01:58,405
My nanny told me that you knew where Xiaoyou went.

25
00:01:58,405 --> 00:02:00,859
Someone must have found Xiaoyou.

26
00:02:00,859 --> 00:02:03,875
Let's go look for it at the lost and found.

27
00:02:03,875 --> 00:02:05,320
Sure.

28
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:07,660
Let's go.

29
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:10,759
Have a seat.

30
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:13,199
Let me show you the photo.

31
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:16,299
- Is this the doll you're looking for?
- Yes, this is the one.

32
00:02:16,299 --> 00:02:18,860
Have you seen the doll in this photo?

33
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:21,379
It looks very familiar. Let me search for it.

34
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,235
Is it the doll you're looking for?

35
00:02:24,235 --> 00:02:26,359
It's Xiaoyou.

36
00:02:26,359 --> 00:02:31,139
But... I left a stain here. Where did it go?

37
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:37,199
I'm sure someone has washed it.

38
00:02:38,295 --> 00:02:40,352
You're probably right.

39
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,299
Dad.

40
00:02:44,299 --> 00:02:47,759
Dad, I found Xiaoyou.

41
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:49,499
Come to Dad.

42
00:02:49,499 --> 00:02:51,199
Director Sheng.

43
00:02:51,812 --> 00:02:53,591
Are you Yanyan's dad?

44
00:02:53,591 --> 00:02:54,899
Yes.

45
00:02:54,899 --> 00:02:58,119
Thank you for keeping her company yesterday.

46
00:02:58,119 --> 00:02:59,960
Besides, you've also put in so much effort today

47
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,333
to help my daughter find Youyou.

48
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:12,559
I think there must be some misunderstandings

49
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:14,519
regarding the contract previously.

50
00:03:14,519 --> 00:03:17,599
Should we talk about it again some other day?

51
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:23,159
Dad, can I spend another day here?

52
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:26,479
They are my new adult friends.

53
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:28,740
But... Dad has work to do.

54
00:03:28,740 --> 00:03:32,779
It's fine. Later, my "son-in-law" will send me home.

55
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:34,679
"Son-in-law"?

56
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:45,679
This place is so beautiful.

57
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:54,039
I guess she has had a long day.

58
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:55,819
Thank you so much.

59
00:03:55,819 --> 00:03:58,679
You had to spend an entire day with Yanyan.

60
00:03:58,679 --> 00:04:01,399
Should I send her home?

61
00:04:01,399 --> 00:04:03,819
I'll send both of you home.

62
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,099
Why are you staring at me?

63
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:17,139
Just ask if you have any questions.

64
00:04:17,139 --> 00:04:20,598
I thought you didn't like kids.

65
00:04:20,598 --> 00:04:25,779
Why does it feel as if you're unwilling to leave Yanyan?

66
00:04:25,779 --> 00:04:28,679
Do you think I stayed here today for her?

67
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:42,599
I need to take a breather.

68
00:04:51,364 --> 00:04:53,143
I'll send Yanyan home.

69
00:04:53,143 --> 00:04:54,939
I'll wait for you here.

70
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,909
Yanyan, it's time to go home.

71
00:05:16,521 --> 00:05:18,920
She is such a good girl.

72
00:05:25,540 --> 00:05:27,758
- Hey, Old Mo.
- Hey, Yi.

73
00:05:27,758 --> 00:05:29,620
Your test result is out.

74
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:33,977
Also, I found a new way to cure you,

75
00:05:33,977 --> 00:05:36,009
but it comes with a very high risk.

76
00:05:36,009 --> 00:05:37,742
How risky is it?

77
00:05:40,363 --> 00:05:42,502
You might lose your life.

78
00:05:57,523 --> 00:06:00,022
Calm down.

79
00:06:08,103 --> 00:06:11,982
Congratulations. They didn't find any organic pathological changes in your brain.

80
00:06:11,982 --> 00:06:15,722
Besides, the report shows that you're exceptionally healthy.

81
00:06:15,722 --> 00:06:16,982
There's only one major issue.

82
00:06:16,983 --> 00:06:19,202
Did Lin show up recently?

83
00:06:19,943 --> 00:06:23,302
I've kept Jing Zhixia by my side, and Lin hasn't shown up since.

84
00:06:23,302 --> 00:06:26,210
In other words, as long as you don't upset Lin,

85
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:28,923
he won't show up again.

86
00:06:28,923 --> 00:06:30,882
Your condition is quite stable.

87
00:06:30,883 --> 00:06:33,962
I don't think you should go through the new therapy I mentioned.

88
00:06:33,963 --> 00:06:37,463
You said that if I undergo the new therapy,

89
00:06:37,463 --> 00:06:39,602
there's a chance that I might die.

90
00:06:39,602 --> 00:06:41,282
What do you mean by that?

91
00:06:41,282 --> 00:06:45,162
After all, all treatment comes with risks.

92
00:06:45,162 --> 00:06:47,470
That's exactly what I meant.

93
00:07:00,563 --> 00:07:04,382
Old Mo, you're the only person in this world who knows about my condition.

94
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:08,302
No matter how severe my condition is, I hope you can be frank with me.

95
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:21,142
Don't worry. You're fine.

96
00:07:21,142 --> 00:07:23,802
It's hard to come across a rare case like yours.

97
00:07:23,803 --> 00:07:26,362
I won't let you die so easily.

98
00:07:26,362 --> 00:07:27,707
A rare case?

99
00:07:27,707 --> 00:07:30,506
Do you want to try the new treatment?

100
00:07:35,423 --> 00:07:38,723
I only want to know what consequence I have to bear

101
00:07:38,723 --> 00:07:42,002
if I decide to go with this treatment.

102
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:49,235
This new therapy might be able to eliminate your alter ego.

103
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:53,214
However, there's only a 50% success rate.

104
00:07:53,214 --> 00:07:57,374
If it works, you'll be freed from Lin forever.

105
00:07:57,374 --> 00:08:01,925
However, if it fails, you'll die and Lin will live.

106
00:08:01,925 --> 00:08:04,702
Fu Zeyi will be gone forever.

107
00:08:04,703 --> 00:08:06,882
It's been some time since Lin last showed up.

108
00:08:06,882 --> 00:08:08,882
It also means

109
00:08:09,763 --> 00:08:12,460
that he'll never show himself again,

110
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:14,582
if I stop upsetting him.

111
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:20,412
You're probably right.

112
00:08:20,412 --> 00:08:23,662
Look. Aren't you doing fine now?

113
00:08:25,803 --> 00:08:30,302
Perhaps you'll never get to perform that treatment on me.

114
00:08:33,493 --> 00:08:36,252
If you want a guinea pig, look for someone else.

115
00:08:36,252 --> 00:08:38,032
Don't get me involved in this.

116
00:08:38,032 --> 00:08:41,332
Is that what you're going to do to the only guy who's been keeping this secret for you?

117
00:08:41,332 --> 00:08:45,272
I'm like a widow, who's preserving...

118
00:08:45,272 --> 00:08:47,208
Her chastity...

119
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:49,341
- Yes. Chastity.
- Your Chinese...

120
00:08:49,341 --> 00:08:51,801
My goodness.

121
00:08:51,801 --> 00:08:53,282
You should date someone.

122
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:56,552
What? Of course, I want to date someone.

123
00:08:57,162 --> 00:09:00,761
But... why are you talking about dating?

124
00:09:01,642 --> 00:09:04,001
Are you seeing someone?

125
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:08,121
Is it the girl who was searching for you in Europe?

126
00:09:08,121 --> 00:09:12,001
However, Lin is a very important person to her.

127
00:09:12,001 --> 00:09:14,541
Do you think you can win her heart?

128
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:17,201
Do you think I'll lose to Lin?

129
00:09:18,302 --> 00:09:20,501
I'll bring you good news soon.

130
00:09:21,742 --> 00:09:23,481
I need to go.

131
00:09:36,481 --> 00:09:40,481
[Fu Zeyi, what was that supposed to mean?]

132
00:09:40,481 --> 00:09:43,741
Jing Zhixia, wake up!

133
00:09:43,741 --> 00:09:48,201
There's an agenda behind every nice thing he does for you.

134
00:09:50,062 --> 00:09:54,001
You can't give in again.
[Fu Zeyi, let's talk.]

135
00:10:11,907 --> 00:10:15,322
Come. Guaiguai.

136
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,171
Eat up.

137
00:10:25,172 --> 00:10:27,391
Why are you not eating?

138
00:10:27,391 --> 00:10:30,811
Isn't this your favorite cat food?

139
00:10:33,772 --> 00:10:36,251
You are really capricious.

140
00:10:39,252 --> 00:10:42,371
Look at this cupboard full of cat food.

141
00:10:42,371 --> 00:10:43,931
Are you kidding me?

142
00:10:43,931 --> 00:10:45,991
You're so capricious.

143
00:10:45,991 --> 00:10:49,651
Do you think I'll continue to like you like a fool?

144
00:10:59,872 --> 00:11:03,891
You will stay here tonight to reflect upon your mistake.

145
00:11:21,952 --> 00:11:24,951
This is the marketing plan I prepared for the next quarter.

146
00:11:24,951 --> 00:11:26,751
Take a look.

147
00:11:29,232 --> 00:11:32,471
Shouldn't I be the one doing this?

148
00:11:34,329 --> 00:11:37,128
I'll return to the Fu Group after the deal with Director Sheng is finalized.

149
00:11:38,041 --> 00:11:40,000
Aizhe still depends on you.

150
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,995
You have to learn how to do this.

151
00:11:41,995 --> 00:11:46,361
Besides, you have to be serious

152
00:11:46,361 --> 00:11:48,242
from the start to the end.

153
00:11:48,242 --> 00:11:50,621
I got it. Thank you.

154
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:55,001
I'll read it later.

155
00:11:55,962 --> 00:11:58,081
Read it now.

156
00:11:58,081 --> 00:12:01,941
Now that I'm here, you can ask me if you have any doubts and I can answer them for you.

157
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:10,340
[Marketing Plan]

158
00:12:14,822 --> 00:12:17,421
It's a very detailed proposal.

159
00:12:20,302 --> 00:12:23,721
Read it all the way to the last page.

160
00:12:26,490 --> 00:12:31,267
[Ticket for a Music Festival]

161
00:12:33,042 --> 00:12:35,421
Are you free tonight?

162
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:37,241
What is this supposed to mean?

163
00:12:37,241 --> 00:12:39,041
Are you asking me out?

164
00:12:43,362 --> 00:12:45,121
Jing Zhixia.

165
00:12:46,002 --> 00:12:50,341
- I...
- I had a crush on you a year ago.

166
00:12:51,262 --> 00:12:55,001
After we reunited, your action proved

167
00:12:55,001 --> 00:12:57,721
that our relationship ended a year ago.

168
00:13:03,882 --> 00:13:05,642
Thank you for not demolishing the hotel.

169
00:13:05,642 --> 00:13:08,061
I helped you yesterday too.

170
00:13:08,061 --> 00:13:10,621
I guess we're even now.

171
00:13:15,762 --> 00:13:18,579
I had a crush on you a year ago.

172
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:21,242
After we reunited, your action proved

173
00:13:21,242 --> 00:13:23,141
that our relationship has ended a year ago.

174
00:13:23,142 --> 00:13:24,862
Lin is a very important person to her.

175
00:13:24,862 --> 00:13:26,781
Do you think you can win her heart?

176
00:13:26,781 --> 00:13:30,161
Sorry, Director Fu. I'm sorry.

177
00:13:33,322 --> 00:13:37,361
Sorry, but the one she likes is me.

178
00:13:37,361 --> 00:13:40,041
Shut up. I'm not going to listen to you.

179
00:13:40,041 --> 00:13:42,461
Sorry. Sorry.

180
00:13:50,022 --> 00:13:52,301
♫  When you sleep soundly at night  ♫

181
00:13:52,301 --> 00:13:57,042
♫ I'm staying awake alone, I'm suffering from endless nightmares ♫

182
00:13:57,042 --> 00:13:59,940
♫  Perhaps once I stop resisting the feelings  ♫

183
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:02,292
[Jing Zhixia likes Lin]

184
00:14:04,261 --> 00:14:09,021
♫  When I open the window to see a night sky without any stars  ♫

185
00:14:09,021 --> 00:14:12,161
♫  I always remember your face  ♫

186
00:14:12,161 --> 00:14:16,201
♫  But I won't expect to see you again  ♫

187
00:14:17,182 --> 00:14:20,081
Sorry, Director Fu. Are you all right?

188
00:14:21,202 --> 00:14:24,142
How can he be all right? She likes me.

189
00:14:24,142 --> 00:14:26,161
I'm sure you're very jealous now, right?

190
00:14:28,062 --> 00:14:30,741
I'm fine.

191
00:14:38,702 --> 00:14:41,041
♫  When you sleep soundly at night  ♫

192
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:46,001
♫  I'm staying awake alone, I'm suffering from endless nightmares  ♫

193
00:14:46,001 --> 00:14:50,982
♫  Perhaps once I stop resisting the feelings, I will fall helplessly for you  ♫

194
00:14:50,982 --> 00:14:52,941
Yi, why are you here?

195
00:14:52,941 --> 00:14:55,081
I have a very important matter to discuss with you.

196
00:14:55,081 --> 00:14:57,681
It's raining heavily out there.

197
00:14:57,681 --> 00:14:59,161
Your shoes are all wet.

198
00:14:59,161 --> 00:15:01,562
Don't sit on my sofa when you're all drenched. Stand right there.

199
00:15:01,562 --> 00:15:03,842
He's back.

200
00:15:03,842 --> 00:15:07,022
- When?
- When?

201
00:15:07,722 --> 00:15:09,881
He's always here.

202
00:15:12,742 --> 00:15:15,661
This shouldn't happen.

203
00:15:15,661 --> 00:15:18,201
It's only been two days. How could it deteriorate so quickly?

204
00:15:18,201 --> 00:15:19,981
I've no idea.

205
00:15:20,592 --> 00:15:23,032
Whatever I'm doing, he is always there.

206
00:15:23,032 --> 00:15:25,251
He even tried to provoke me.

207
00:15:25,251 --> 00:15:27,931
He told me that Jing Zhixia loves him, not me.

208
00:15:27,931 --> 00:15:32,071
Why doesn't it sound like your usual symptoms?

209
00:15:32,071 --> 00:15:34,058
It doesn't sound like you're sick.

210
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:36,087
It's more like you're heartbroken.

211
00:15:36,087 --> 00:15:40,483
Could it be that Lin is your imaginary love rival?

212
00:15:40,483 --> 00:15:43,252
Did Jing Zhixia admit that she likes Lin?

213
00:15:43,252 --> 00:15:44,911
That's impossible.

214
00:15:44,911 --> 00:15:48,151
Their relationship ended a year ago.

215
00:15:48,151 --> 00:15:52,631
But for Jing Zhixia, you're Lin.

216
00:15:52,631 --> 00:15:56,231
She turned you down. Am I right?

217
00:15:59,712 --> 00:16:02,291
Not exactly. I haven't confessed my feelings to her.

218
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:03,911
She never gave me a chance to explain myself.

219
00:16:03,911 --> 00:16:06,271
She didn't even allow you to explain yourself.

220
00:16:06,271 --> 00:16:07,571
This is not going to work.

221
00:16:07,571 --> 00:16:10,651
I'm talking to you about Lin. What are you talking about?

222
00:16:10,651 --> 00:16:14,611
The symptoms you're showing are beyond my area of expertise.

223
00:16:14,611 --> 00:16:18,511
I think you should make a real confession.

224
00:16:18,511 --> 00:16:22,391
That's the only way to cure your lovesickness.

225
00:16:22,391 --> 00:16:24,871
Lovesickness?

226
00:16:24,871 --> 00:16:26,511
That's rubbish.

227
00:16:26,511 --> 00:16:28,472
It's definitely lovesickness.

228
00:16:28,472 --> 00:16:31,851
Look. You're always thinking about her. How is this not lovesickness?

229
00:16:31,851 --> 00:16:34,251
I told you so.

230
00:16:36,192 --> 00:16:39,091
Sister, let's have a meal together after work.

231
00:16:39,091 --> 00:16:41,931
I heard that there's a new restaurant near the hotel. It has received pretty good reviews.

232
00:16:41,931 --> 00:16:43,632
I don't think I can make it today.

233
00:16:43,632 --> 00:16:47,731
My mom is back. She told me that she's getting married next month.

234
00:16:47,731 --> 00:16:50,751
She kept asking me to pick a wedding gown with Ye Ming.

235
00:16:50,751 --> 00:16:52,072
What?

236
00:16:52,072 --> 00:16:54,472
Are you going to pick a wedding gown with Ye Ming?

237
00:16:54,472 --> 00:16:58,751
You can't do that. A wedding is a once-in-a-lifetime thing, Sister.

238
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:01,698
I know. It's giving me a headache.

239
00:17:01,698 --> 00:17:04,031
Do you know any bridal boutiques? I want a famous one.

240
00:17:04,031 --> 00:17:06,591
I think I have a friend who runs a high-class bridal boutique.

241
00:17:06,591 --> 00:17:09,371
If I remember it correctly, it's called "Dear Wedding Boutique."

242
00:17:09,371 --> 00:17:11,911
It's located at Central Square.

243
00:17:14,332 --> 00:17:17,431
Director Fu. This is the timber supplier we're going to meet later at the meal.

244
00:17:17,431 --> 00:17:20,551
Jian Bufan. Are you there?

245
00:17:20,551 --> 00:17:22,291
I'll send you the location later.

246
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,432
We're almost done with the provisional contract.

247
00:17:24,432 --> 00:17:26,712
You might need to confirm it for one final time.

248
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:29,231
I'll get it delivered to you later.

249
00:17:30,912 --> 00:17:32,531
Director Fu.

250
00:17:35,832 --> 00:17:39,811
She didn't tell you that she was going for a wedding dress fitting with another man.

251
00:17:39,811 --> 00:17:41,911
I think

252
00:17:42,792 --> 00:17:45,191
she doesn't care about you at all.

253
00:17:46,352 --> 00:17:47,931
Director Fu.

254
00:17:51,652 --> 00:17:54,592
The supplier is arriving soon. Can you get the car from the basement?

255
00:17:54,592 --> 00:17:57,492
- I'll be waiting for you at the front door.
- Sure.

256
00:18:00,172 --> 00:18:02,771
